This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney on March 20, 2014. Carney is joined by Betsey Stevenson, a member of the President's Council of Economic Advisers, to discuss the President's upcoming events and roundtable discussions on working families. The events are part of a series leading up to the Working Families Summit on June 23rd. The goal is to gather input from real people, businesses, state and local governments, and members of Congress to address the needs of working families in the changing labor force. The article also mentions the President's announcement of new sanctions on Russia in response to their actions in Ukraine. It also briefly mentions the President's statement on the ongoing search for the missing Malaysia Airlines plane and the involvement of the FBI.